{
  "stem": "1918.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They came so swiftly, all those orders.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was almost impossible to keep up with the speed of it because, as I told you, whatever they learned throughout the years-- how to refine the method-- was absolutely perfect by the time they reached Hungary-- the yellow star, the wearing of a yellow star, of how many inches it has to be, how it has to be sewn on so you can't tear it off.",
      "word_count": 67
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course!",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everybody had to.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Every Jew.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the left, we wore it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Other countries, evidently, wore it in the front and in the back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had to wear ours on the left side.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother was busy--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course we had to buy the cloth, and my mother was busy sewing the yellow stars.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you know, all of this-- at the start of all this, I must tell you, that we lived in a fascist country, in a hateful terrible place, with anti-Semites worse than probably in Germany or, you know, probably worse, and, and then, as in Poland, incredible anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So Hitler had a very easy time in my country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But also because we lived in a fascist country with a controlled press, controlled radio, we knew only, only what Hitler wanted us to know.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We have never heard the name of a town called Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We never knew anything at all what happened.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Hitler was winning the war, and we were supposed to root for Hitler.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we incessantly heard him on the radio, and all the anti-Semites and all Hitler lovers were shouting, heil Hitler, heil Hitler.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we grew up with that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We thought that that was normal kind of because it lasted for so many years in our young adulthood.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
